To add the AC1 and AC2 functionality, you can create a separate Utils class with a method for setting the JobStatus to FLINK_JOB_SUBMITTED or FLINK_JOB_FAILED. Here's an example implementation:

Utils.java:

```java
public class Utils {
    public static void setJobStatus(UnifiedAuditMessage auditMsg, JobStatus jobStatus) {
        auditMsg.setJobStatus(jobStatus);
    }
}
```

Then, you can use this Utils class in the FlinkApiController class to set the JobStatus accordingly:

FlinkApiController.java:

```java
@Service
public class FlinkApiController {

    // ...

    private KafkaConsumer kafkaConsumer = new KafkaConsumer();
    @Autowired
    private KafkaAuditProducer kafkaAuditProducer;
    @Autowired
    private Utils utils;

    // ...

    public String triggerJob(UnifiedAuditMessage auditMsg, String fileType) {
        // ...

        if (response != null && response.getStatusCode() != HttpStatus.OK) {
            // AC1: Transformation job submission is successful
            utils.setJobStatus(auditMsg, JobStatus.FLINK_JOB_SUBMITTED);

            return "Job submitted";
        } else {
            // AC2: Transformation job submission is NOT successful
            utils.setJobStatus(auditMsg, JobStatus.FLINK_JOB_FAILED);

            UnifiedAuditMessage auditData = kafkaConsumer.logMetadata(auditMsg, fileType, response);
            kafkaAuditProducer.createMessageAndLog(auditMsg.getInputFilePath(), auditMsg.getUrl(), auditMsg.getPort(),
                auditMsg.getOutputFilePath(), auditMsg.getDelimiters(), fileType,
                new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss").format(new Date()),
                auditMsg.getNo_of_records_in_the_file(), auditMsg.getNo_of_records_processed(),
                auditMsg.getNo_of_records_failed(), auditMsg.getExceptions(), auditMsg.getJob_id(),
                auditMsg.getJar_id(), auditMsg.getCollector_id());

            kafkaConsumer.writeLogToFile(auditMsg, fileType, response, logFolderPath);
        }
        
        // ...
    }

    // ...
}

```

Hope this helps! Let me know if you have any further questions.